Line Plot – for time series trends (e.g., COVID-19 cases over time).

Bar Chart – comparisons across regions/countries.

Pie Chart – proportions (used sparingly).

Heatmaps – correlation matrix.

Box Plot – spotting outliers in data.

Use clear, simple charts with titles and labels.

    Line plot: trends over time.

    Bar chart: comparisons.

    Pie chart: proportions.

    Heatmap: correlation.
